Defendant in custody.
EXHIBIT 1, copy of discipline report from Manitowoc County Jail.
The court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of four and one-half (4.5) years.  That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision.
The Court finds the defendant NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Defendant is to participate in the batterers treatment group;
3) Have no contact with the victim, Cassandra Nenahalo;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
7) Undergo an anger management assessment and follow through;
8) undergo a mental health assessment and follow through.
The defendant has credit for 301 days.
Minutes.

The State files an Amended Information which amends count 1 to misdemeanor bail jumping, contrary to Section 946.49(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge in count 1 of 14 CF 483, misdemeanor bail jumping.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge of strangulation and suffocation in count 3 of 14 CF 483. Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2, 4, 5 and 6; bail jumping, battery, disorderly conduct and resist officer.  Motion granted.
On count 1, misdemeanor bail jumping, the defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for eighty (80) days, time already served.
Defendant has credit for 63 days.  (11-06-14 to 01-07-15)
Court costs are waived.
On count 3, strangulation/suffocation, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Defendant is to participate in the batterers treatment group;
3) No contact with the victim, Cassandra Nenahalo;
4) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 03-19-15 by 5:00 p.m.;
5) Spend an additional sixty (60) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) maintain fulltime employment or work search.
